      • writeUndirectedMultigraph

        public <T,E extends TypedEdge<T>> void writeUndirectedMultigraph(Multigraph<T,E> g,
                                                        File f,
                                                        Map<T,Color> edgeColors)
                               throws IOException
        Writes the provided multigraph to the specified DOT file, using edgeColors as a guide for how to display parallel edges of different types.
        Parameters:
        f - the file where the DOT graph will be written. Any existing file contents will be overwritten
        edgeColor - a mapping from an edge type to a color. Types that do not have colors will be randomly assigned one and the edgeColors map will be updated appropriately.
        Throws:
        IOException

                               throws IOException
        Writes the provided multigraph to the specified DOT file, using edgeColors as a guide for how to display parallel edges of different types.
        Parameters:
        f - the file where the DOT graph will be written. Any existing file contents will be overwritten
        edgeColor - a mapping from an edge type to a color. Types that do not have colors will be randomly assigned one and the edgeColors map will be updated appropriately.
        Throws:
        IOException
